Whooee!  Doc, you have just been hammered again! I think that objections are fair but this thing with you and Cook go WAY beyond that. (Don't compare me to that peanut farmer)&lt;G&gt;<br><br>
Get some space between you and Cook.  Gook is a word in the American idiom. It was first used in Korea.  It is not new to vets.  Granted it is a racist word like the others sometimes used to described other minorities.  In SoCal the racial word used most often is &quot;gringo&quot;.  Or &quot;flaco&quot;, or any thing else you want to use.  Gook is part of the Vietnam vet vocabulary. It is as much part of &quot;our&quot; language as is the term &quot;wasted&quot; or &quot;deros&quot; or &quot;16&quot; or &quot;20mm&quot; or &quot;thumper&quot; or &quot;slick&quot; or &quot;Doc&quot;. It is real, it isn't nice but it is factual.  If you can apply a perjoritive to something, when it is used it doesn't have as much meaning.  I would have a REAL difficult time saying, &quot;I killed 20 human beings today&quot;. It is easier to process that I killed 20 &quot;gooks&quot;. Still doesn't make it right. <br><br>
Perhaps that is why &quot;it don't mean nuthin'&quot;.  Or Xin Loi..or Sorry about that.
